<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued July 07 at 3:52PM MDT until July 07 at 4:15PM MDT by NWS Pueblo</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 415 PM MDT
FOR EAST CENTRAL HUERFANO AND NORTHWESTERN LAS ANIMAS COUNTIES...
At 352 PM MDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Walsenburg, or
22 miles east of Indian Creek on the southeastern Spring Burn Scar,
moving southeast at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Quarter size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Damage to vehicles is expected.
Locations impacted include...
Walsenburg.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...1.00 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;50 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
